<p>West Side neighborhoods like Hilldale and Midvale Heights typically feature newer construction with better roof orientations for solar panels and more standardized HVAC system installations. The Far West Side, including areas like Gammon Road and Mineral Point, offers newer homes with optimal roof space for larger solar arrays and modern HVAC infrastructure. East Side neighborhoods such as Atwood and Schenk-Atwood-Starkweather-Yahara provide excellent solar potential with many south-facing roofs, while North Side areas like Northport and Sherman often feature larger lots that accommodate ground-mounted solar systems and geothermal installations.</p>

